[
  {
    "text": "Concrete is the most widely used",
    "start": 7.02,
    "duration": 1.82
  },
  {
    "text": "construction material in the world.",
    "start": 8.84,
    "duration": 2.08
  },
  {
    "text": "It can be found in swathes of city pavements,",
    "start": 10.92,
    "duration": 2.55
  },
  {
    "text": "bridges that span vast rivers,",
    "start": 13.47,
    "duration": 2.51
  },
  {
    "text": "and the tallest skyscrapers on earth.",
    "start": 15.99,
    "duration": 2.23
  },
  {
    "text": "But this sturdy substance",
    "start": 18.22,
    "duration": 1.55
  },
  {
    "text": "does have a weakness:",
    "start": 19.77,
    "duration": 1.36
  },
  {
    "text": "it’s prone to catastrophic cracking",
    "start": 21.13,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "that costs tens of billions of dollars",
    "start": 22.84,
    "duration": 1.7
  },
  {
    "text": "to repair each year.",
    "start": 24.54,
    "duration": 1.59
  },
  {
    "text": "But what if we could avoid that problem,",
    "start": 26.13,
    "duration": 2.16
  },
  {
    "text": "by creating concrete that heals itself?",
    "start": 28.29,
    "duration": 3.02
  },
  {
    "text": "This idea isn’t as far-fetched",
    "start": 31.31,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "as it may seem.",
    "start": 32.77,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "It boils down to an understanding",
    "start": 33.92,
    "duration": 1.843
  },
  {
    "text": "of how concrete forms,",
    "start": 35.763,
    "duration": 1.69
  },
  {
    "text": "and how to exploit that process",
    "start": 37.453,
    "duration": 1.79
  },
  {
    "text": "to our benefit.",
    "start": 39.243,
    "duration": 1.39
  },
  {
    "text": "Concrete is a combination of coarse stone",
    "start": 40.648,
    "duration": 2.15
  },
  {
    "text": "and sand particles, called aggregates,",
    "start": 42.798,
    "duration": 2.348
  },
  {
    "text": "that mix with cement, a powdered blend",
    "start": 45.146,
    "duration": 2.43
  },
  {
    "text": "of clay and limestone.",
    "start": 47.576,
    "duration": 1.66
  },
  {
    "text": "When water gets added to this mix,",
    "start": 49.245,
    "duration": 1.94
  },
  {
    "text": "the cement forms a paste and",
    "start": 51.185,
    "duration": 1.63
  },
  {
    "text": "coats the aggregates, quickly hardening",
    "start": 52.815,
    "duration": 2.23
  },
  {
    "text": "through a chemical reaction",
    "start": 55.045,
    "duration": 1.23
  },
  {
    "text": "called hydration.",
    "start": 56.275,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "Eventually, the resulting material",
    "start": 58.077,
    "duration": 1.86
  },
  {
    "text": "grows strong enough to prop up buildings",
    "start": 59.937,
    "duration": 2.31
  },
  {
    "text": "that climb hundreds of meters",
    "start": 62.247,
    "duration": 1.45
  },
  {
    "text": "into the sky.",
    "start": 63.697,
    "duration": 1.44
  },
  {
    "text": "While people have been using",
    "start": 65.137,
    "duration": 1.162
  },
  {
    "text": "a variety of recipes to produce cement",
    "start": 66.299,
    "duration": 1.98
  },
  {
    "text": "for over 4,000 years,",
    "start": 68.283,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "concrete itself",
    "start": 70.283,
    "duration": 0.996
  },
  {
    "text": "has a surprisingly short lifespan.",
    "start": 71.279,
    "duration": 2.63
  },
  {
    "text": "After 20 to 30 years,",
    "start": 73.914,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "natural processes like concrete shrinkage,",
    "start": 75.624,
    "duration": 2.95
  },
  {
    "text": "excessive freezing and thawing,",
    "start": 78.574,
    "duration": 1.76
  },
  {
    "text": "and heavy loads can trigger cracking.",
    "start": 80.334,
    "duration": 3.18
  },
  {
    "text": "And it’s not just big breaks that count:",
    "start": 83.514,
    "duration": 2.48
  },
  {
    "text": "tiny cracks can be just as dangerous.",
    "start": 85.994,
    "duration": 2.4
  },
  {
    "text": "Concrete is often used",
    "start": 88.404,
    "duration": 1.64
  },
  {
    "text": "as a secondary support",
    "start": 90.044,
    "duration": 1.42
  },
  {
    "text": "around steel reinforcements.",
    "start": 91.464,
    "duration": 2.18
  },
  {
    "text": "In this concrete, even small cracks",
    "start": 93.644,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "can channel water, oxygen,",
    "start": 95.854,
    "duration": 2.09
  },
  {
    "text": "and carbon dioxide that corrode the steel",
    "start": 97.944,
    "duration": 2.85
  },
  {
    "text": "and lead to disastrous collapse.",
    "start": 100.794,
    "duration": 2.56
  },
  {
    "text": "On structures like bridges and highways",
    "start": 103.354,
    "duration": 1.91
  },
  {
    "text": "that are constantly in use,",
    "start": 105.264,
    "duration": 1.67
  },
  {
    "text": "detecting these problems",
    "start": 106.934,
    "duration": 1.41
  },
  {
    "text": "before they lead to catastrophe",
    "start": 108.344,
    "duration": 1.82
  },
  {
    "text": "becomes a huge and costly challenge.",
    "start": 110.164,
    "duration": 2.15
  },
  {
    "text": "But not doing so",
    "start": 112.314,
    "duration": 1.48
  },
  {
    "text": "would also endanger thousands of lives.",
    "start": 113.794,
    "duration": 2.77
  },
  {
    "text": "Fortunately, we’re already experimenting",
    "start": 116.564,
    "duration": 2.47
  },
  {
    "text": "with ways this material",
    "start": 119.034,
    "duration": 1.32
  },
  {
    "text": "could start fixing itself.",
    "start": 120.354,
    "duration": 1.77
  },
  {
    "text": "And some of these solutions",
    "start": 122.124,
    "duration": 1.25
  },
  {
    "text": "are inspired by concrete’s",
    "start": 123.374,
    "duration": 1.37
  },
  {
    "text": "natural self-healing mechanism.",
    "start": 124.744,
    "duration": 2.11
  },
  {
    "text": "When water enters these tiny cracks,",
    "start": 126.859,
    "duration": 2.26
  },
  {
    "text": "it hydrates the concrete’s calcium oxide.",
    "start": 129.119,
    "duration": 2.99
  },
  {
    "text": "The resulting calcium hydroxide",
    "start": 132.109,
    "duration": 1.87
  },
  {
    "text": "reacts with carbon dioxide in the air,",
    "start": 133.979,
    "duration": 2.4
  },
  {
    "text": "starting a process called",
    "start": 136.379,
    "duration": 1.41
  },
  {
    "text": "autogenous healing, where",
    "start": 137.789,
    "duration": 1.77
  },
  {
    "text": "microscopic calcium carbonate crystals",
    "start": 139.559,
    "duration": 2.26
  },
  {
    "text": "form and gradually fill the gap.",
    "start": 141.819,
    "duration": 2.44
  },
  {
    "text": "Unfortunately, these crystals",
    "start": 144.259,
    "duration": 1.9
  },
  {
    "text": "can only do so much, healing cracks",
    "start": 146.159,
    "duration": 2.59
  },
  {
    "text": "that are less than 0.3mm wide.",
    "start": 148.749,
    "duration": 2.98
  },
  {
    "text": "Material scientists have figured out how",
    "start": 151.729,
    "duration": 1.86
  },
  {
    "text": "to heal cracks up to twice that size by",
    "start": 153.589,
    "duration": 2.06
  },
  {
    "text": "adding hidden glue into the concrete mix.",
    "start": 155.649,
    "duration": 2.53
  },
  {
    "text": "If we put adhesive-filled fibers",
    "start": 158.179,
    "duration": 1.89
  },
  {
    "text": "and tubes into the mixture,",
    "start": 160.069,
    "duration": 1.49
  },
  {
    "text": "they’ll snap open when a crack forms,",
    "start": 161.559,
    "duration": 2.52
  },
  {
    "text": "releasing their sticky contents",
    "start": 164.079,
    "duration": 1.86
  },
  {
    "text": "and sealing the gap.",
    "start": 165.939,
    "duration": 1.57
  },
  {
    "text": "But adhesive chemicals often behave",
    "start": 167.509,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "very differently from concrete,",
    "start": 169.469,
    "duration": 1.5
  },
  {
    "text": "and over time, these adhesives",
    "start": 170.969,
    "duration": 1.74
  },
  {
    "text": "can lead to even worse cracks.",
    "start": 172.709,
    "duration": 2.5
  },
  {
    "text": "So perhaps the best way to heal",
    "start": 175.209,
    "duration": 1.69
  },
  {
    "text": "large cracks is to give concrete",
    "start": 176.899,
    "duration": 2.16
  },
  {
    "text": "the tools to help itself.",
    "start": 179.059,
    "duration": 2.08
  },
  {
    "text": "Scientists have discovered that",
    "start": 181.139,
    "duration": 1.15
  },
  {
    "text": "some bacteria and fungi",
    "start": 182.289,
    "duration": 1.58
  },
  {
    "text": "can produce minerals,",
    "start": 183.879,
    "duration": 1.58
  },
  {
    "text": "including the calcium carbonate",
    "start": 185.459,
    "duration": 1.97
  },
  {
    "text": "found in autogenous healing.",
    "start": 187.429,
    "duration": 2.03
  },
  {
    "text": "Experimental blends of concrete",
    "start": 189.459,
    "duration": 1.61
  },
  {
    "text": "include these bacterial or fungal spores",
    "start": 191.069,
    "duration": 2.36
  },
  {
    "text": "alongside nutrients in their concrete mix,",
    "start": 193.429,
    "duration": 2.55
  },
  {
    "text": "where they could lie dormant",
    "start": 195.979,
    "duration": 1.27
  },
  {
    "text": "for hundreds of years.",
    "start": 197.249,
    "duration": 1.75
  },
  {
    "text": "When cracks finally appear",
    "start": 198.999,
    "duration": 1.33
  },
  {
    "text": "and water trickles into the concrete,",
    "start": 200.329,
    "duration": 1.77
  },
  {
    "text": "the spores germinate, grow, and consume",
    "start": 202.099,
    "duration": 3.11
  },
  {
    "text": "the nutrient soup that surrounds them,",
    "start": 205.209,
    "duration": 2.22
  },
  {
    "text": "modifying their local environment",
    "start": 207.429,
    "duration": 1.6
  },
  {
    "text": "to create the perfect conditions",
    "start": 209.029,
    "duration": 1.78
  },
  {
    "text": "for calcium carbonate to grow.",
    "start": 210.809,
    "duration": 2.45
  },
  {
    "text": "These crystals gradually fill the gaps,",
    "start": 213.259,
    "duration": 2.07
  },
  {
    "text": "and after roughly three weeks,",
    "start": 215.329,
    "duration": 1.51
  },
  {
    "text": "the hard-working microbes",
    "start": 216.839,
    "duration": 1.38
  },
  {
    "text": "can completely repair cracks",
    "start": 218.219,
    "duration": 1.7
  },
  {
    "text": "up to almost 1mm wide.",
    "start": 219.919,
    "duration": 2.78
  },
  {
    "text": "When the cracks seal,",
    "start": 222.699,
    "duration": 1.17
  },
  {
    "text": "the bacteria or fungi will make spores",
    "start": 223.869,
    "duration": 2.18
  },
  {
    "text": "and go dormant once more—",
    "start": 226.049,
    "duration": 1.52
  },
  {
    "text": "ready to start a new cycle of self-healing",
    "start": 227.569,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "when cracks form again.",
    "start": 229.849,
    "duration": 1.43
  },
  {
    "text": "Although this technique",
    "start": 231.689,
    "duration": 1.02
  },
  {
    "text": "has been studied extensively,",
    "start": 232.709,
    "duration": 1.64
  },
  {
    "text": "we still have a ways to go",
    "start": 234.349,
    "duration": 1.34
  },
  {
    "text": "before incorporating it",
    "start": 235.689,
    "duration": 1.18
  },
  {
    "text": "in the global production of concrete.",
    "start": 236.869,
    "duration": 2.04
  },
  {
    "text": "But, these spores have huge potential",
    "start": 238.963,
    "duration": 2.54
  },
  {
    "text": "to make concrete",
    "start": 241.503,
    "duration": 0.9
  },
  {
    "text": "more resilient and long-lasting—",
    "start": 242.403,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "which could drastically reduce",
    "start": 244.683,
    "duration": 1.48
  },
  {
    "text": "the financial and environmental cost",
    "start": 246.163,
    "duration": 2.3
  },
  {
    "text": "of concrete production.",
    "start": 248.463,
    "duration": 1.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Eventually, these microorganisms",
    "start": 250.303,
    "duration": 2.47
  },
  {
    "text": "may force us to reconsider",
    "start": 252.773,
    "duration": 1.41
  },
  {
    "text": "the way we think about our cities,",
    "start": 254.183,
    "duration": 1.94
  },
  {
    "text": "bringing our inanimate concrete jungles",
    "start": 256.123,
    "duration": 2.01
  },
  {
    "text": "to life.",
    "start": 258.133,
    "duration": 1.11
  }
]